>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"measuring-guide\">\n        <h2>HOW TO MEASURE FOR JACKETS</h2>\n        <div class=\"measuring-grid\">\n          <div class=\"measuring-item\">\n            <h3>BUST/CHEST</h3>\n            <p>Measure around the fullest part of your bust/chest with arms relaxed at your sides. Keep the tape parallel to the floor.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"measuring-item\">\n            <h3>SHOULDER WIDTH</h3>\n            <p>Measure from the edge of one shoulder to the edge of the other, across the back at the widest point.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"measuring-item\">\n            <h3>SLEEVE LENGTH</h3>\n            <p>With arm slightly bent, measure from the center back of the neck, across the shoulder, down to the wrist bone.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"measuring-item\">\n            <h3>JACKET LENGTH</h3>\n            <p>Measure from the highest point of the shoulder (where it meets the neck) straight down to where you want the jacket to end.</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"fit-tips\">\n        <h2>JACKET FIT TIPS</h2>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Between sizes? Size up for a more relaxed fit or to layer over thicker garments.</li>\n          <li>Our jackets are designed with a modern, tailored silhouette that's not too boxy or tight.</li>\n          <li>Shoulders should sit comfortably without pulling or sagging.</li>\n          <li>Sleeves should end at your wrist bone, or slightly above for a cropped style.</li>\n          <li>You should be able to comfortably button/zip the jacket with room for layering.</li>\n          <li>Check individual product pages for specific fit notes (slim fit, regular fit, oversized, etc.).</li>\n          <li>All measurements are approximate and may vary slightly by jacket style.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"size-help\">\n        <h3>STILL UNSURE?</h3>\n        <p>Our customer service 